					<head>Prophets</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79054379  lccn.loc.gov/n80008477" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Former Prophets with Targum, punctuated, with masorah magna and parva.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr ar">Hebrew, Aramaic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80008477">
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Nevi᾿im </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">נביאים</title>
							<locus from="1v" to="217v"/>
							<note>
								<p>Folio 216v contains a subscription in a later hand, which may be a copy of the original subscription of the manuscript.</p>
								<p>Judges 4:23-5:31 have also an Arabic translation.</p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Written by the same hand as Or 1474 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">139</ref>) and similar to Or 1471 (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">130</ref>), which is dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1589</date>. This volume is a companion to Or 1474, which contains the Latter Prophets.</filiation>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">ותהי השלמתו יום שלישי י"ח יום לחדש מרחשון שנת א'ת'ת'ק'נ'ד' במאתא מעבר ת'ו' ות'ו'ב'י'ר'.<locus n="216v"/>
							</colophon>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1v" to="32v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Joshua</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<title xml:lang="en">Judges</title>
								<locus from="32v" to="65r"/>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<title xml:lang="en">Samuel</title>
								<locus from="65v" to="140v"/>
								<note>
									<p>2Samuel starts on folio 107r.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<title xml:lang="en">Kings</title>
								<locus from="141r" to="216v"/>
								<note>
									<p>2Kings starts on folio 180r.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>217 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>311</height>
										<width>203</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>217 folios. </p>
									<p>Original foliation in Hebrew letters. </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>22 quires of 10 leaves each, apart from the last of 7 leaves only. </p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last page (lost after 11th quire). </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Folios 1-3, 209-215 are imperfectly preserved. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Masorah magna occupies generally two lines in the upper and one to four lines in the lower margin of the page. </p>
									<p>The titles of the books are written on the verso of each leaf in the upper margin. </p>
									<p>A number of masoretic notes is given at the end of each books. </p>
									<p>The beginning and the end of the Hafṭarot are indicated in the margin. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary> Yemenite square script, punctuated. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major">
								<p>
									<locus from="216" to="217"/>due to later hands.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 217r-217v contain doodles. </p>
							<p>Comments of a non-masoretic character are found throughout, e.g. 42v, 45r.  </p>
							<p>A Hebrew subscription on folio 216v, with a date of <date calendar="Seleucid">18 Marheshvan 1954</date>, i.e. <date calendar="Gregorian">1642</date>, and the name of the city of <name type="place">Ma'abar</name>, due to a later hand. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Aharon ha-Kohen</name>, inscribed with his name on folio 1r. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house. </p>
								<p>Spine: 'Former Prophets with Targum. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2371.' </p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
